  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6600.11 sitting just below the massive +16174M gamma wall at 6605, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher into that level while simultaneously providing support on dips toward the -8706M negative gamma at 6590. The PIN regime with 25.6B in total GEX creates a strong mean-reversion setup between these key strikes, with dealers acting as stabilizers rather than amplifiers. The recent wall break and GEX surge (137% 1-min change) suggests we just saw significant options flow that has dealers scrambling to hedge, likely creating the current resistance at 6605.\n\n**Key levels:** Watch 6605 resistance (dealers sell), 6590 support (dealers buy), and the 6620 flip line above.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to ping-pong between 6590-6605 as dealers keep it rangebound.",
